io.reinert.requestor.core

Interface RequestEvent

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    HttpStatus
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Status, StatusFamily

    public interface RequestEvent
extends Serializable

    Represents an event that may occur during a Request.

    It can be either a Response or a RequestException.

    Author:
    Danilo Reinert

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static RequestEvent ABORT
      Represents a request abort before sending during the processing cycle.
      static RequestEvent CANCEL
      Represents a request cancel before receiving a response.
      static RequestEvent ERROR
      Represents any request error, combining 'timeout', 'cancel' and 'abort' events.
      static RequestEvent FAIL
      Represents a non 2xx response.
      static RequestEvent LOAD
      Represents a response received.
      static RequestEvent SUCCESS
      Represents a 2xx response.
      static RequestEvent TIMEOUT
      Represents a request timeout with no response.
